>
  <p>Jake co-founded River Records to build better software for physicians. He's a practicing internist, Assistant Professor at Tufts University School of Medicine, and a published researcher in clinical informatics and natural language processing.</p>
  <p>His research on duplicate information in the electronic medical record — published in JAMA Network Open — showed that more than half of all text in a large academic health system's chart was copied from prior notes. That finding became the foundation for Stream's problem-oriented approach to clinical documentation.</p>
  <p>When he's not working with River Records or seeing patients, you'll find him coaching his kids on the soccer field, baking bread, or riding his Peloton.</p>
</TeamMember>
